# 🚧 Endpoint Inventory Tasks (WebUI)

## Phase 1 — Build the endpoint matrix (REQ-WEI-1,2) (`@frontend-dev`)

- [ ] Enumerate active routes from `dalogin-quarkus/src/main/resources/META-INF/resources/film-review/app.js`.
- [ ] Map each route to its Angular controller.
- [ ] Extract all API calls per controller (method + path).
- [ ] Produce matrix rows with auth expectation and implementation status.

## Phase 2 — Verify service ownership (REQ-WEI-3,7) (`@frontend-dev` + `@backend-dev` + `@database-dev`)

- [ ] Confirm each endpoint exists in backend controller code.
- [ ] Assign one owner service per endpoint:
  - [ ] `dalogin-quarkus`
  - [ ] `mbooks-quarkus`
  - [ ] `mbook-quarkus`
  - [ ] `simple-service-webapp-quarkus`
- [ ] Flag doc-vs-code mismatches and resolve using code as source of truth.

## Phase 3 — Gap analysis and phase tagging (REQ-WEI-4) (`@frontend-dev` + `@backend-dev`)

- [ ] Mark matrix rows `implemented`, `partial`, or `missing`.
- [ ] Categorize missing/partial endpoints into P1/P2/P3.
- [ ] Identify blockers that would break currently active booking routes.

## Phase 4 — Define extension contracts (REQ-WEI-5) (`@frontend-dev` + `@backend-dev` + `@database-dev`)

- [ ] Add P2 candidate contract for `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/trending-movies`.
- [ ] Add P2 candidate contract for `GET /mbooks-1/rest/book/movies/{movieId}`.
- [ ] Add P2 usage contract for server-side paging/search endpoints.
- [ ] List required response keys expected by Film-Review templates/controllers.

## Phase 5 — Scope guard and route policy (REQ-WEI-6) (`@frontend-dev` + `@backend-dev`)

- [ ] Mark non-booking template modules as disabled-by-default.
- [ ] Define enablement rule: route can be enabled only after endpoint owner + auth + contract are present.
- [ ] Add explicit note for blog/news/celebrity/profile/rating modules.

## Phase 6 — Deliverables and sign-off (REQ-WEI-NF-1,2,3) (`@frontend-dev` + `@backend-dev` + `@devops` + `@ios-dev`)

- [ ] Publish endpoint matrix artifact with callsite references.
- [ ] Publish phased gap list and owner map.
- [ ] Verify `trending-movies` is present in P2 discovery scope.
- [ ] Complete acceptance checklist in `speckit.webui.endpoint-inventory.specify`.

